Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs130\bord0\pos(950,950)\b0\fsp0.4}地         球         脉         动 {\fsp0.5}  I I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.25,0:00:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上四分之一的土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One quarter of all the land on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.14,0:00:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖着唯一一种伟大的植被\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is covered by a single, remarkable type of plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们几乎坚不可摧  一天可以长高六十厘米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Almost indestructible, it can grow two feet in a day...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连巨型动物都能藏匿其中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And be tall enough to hide a giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.77,0:01:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是草本\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That plant is grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.46,0:01:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草本植物构建出来的世界独具一格\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the world it creates is truly unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,印度北部的草是地球上长得最高的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The grass in northern India is the tallest on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.90,0:01:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里是众多神奇生物的家园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}home to some of the most impressive creatures to tread the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.84,0:01:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在正当好时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are the good times,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.08,0:01:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可再过几个月  这些青草就会消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but in just a few months, all this fresh growth will be gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.41,0:02:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物们将被迫迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the animals will be forced to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.52,0:02:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的草原都是如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That is the way things are on grasslands across the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.27,0:02:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重复着富足  消亡  重生的循环\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A cycle of abundance, destruction and rebirth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.91,0:02:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从而影响着栖息在这里的所有生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that affects every creature that lives here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)\fs110\bord0\b0\pos(960,480)}草        原
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辽阔的欧亚草原区是地球上最大的草原地带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The largest grassland on Earth, the vast Eurasian Steppe,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.11,0:02:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖距离达到地球周长的三分之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}stretches one third of the way around our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\b0}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.18,0:02:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青草随春雨而生  也带来了新生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Spring rain has brought fresh grass, and with it, new life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一种冰川时代存活至今的生物  高鼻羚羊幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A relic from the Ice Age, a baby Saiga antelope,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.25,0:03:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出生才三小时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}just three hours old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.43,0:03:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陪伴它的只有它的孪生兄弟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His only company, his twin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在它们能站起来之前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Until they can stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.19,0:03:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母亲会将它们藏在草丛中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their mother has left them hidden in the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样应该很安全  只要保持安静\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They should be safe, as long as they remain quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对这两只小羊来说  时间紧迫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For these calves, the clock is already ticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.80,0:03:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,羚羊群很快就要离开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their herd will soon be moving on,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.89,0:03:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去寻找最新鲜的草场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}seeking the freshest new grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高鼻羚羊四肢瘦长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their lanky legs are a sure sign
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.10,0:04:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,预示着它们一生都将奔波在路上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that they're built for a life on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高鼻羚羊总会产下孪生幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Saiga always give birth to twins,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.93,0:04:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样能够在草源充足时迅速繁衍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so their numbers grow rapidly just when grass is plentiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.53,0:04:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的鼻子长相奇怪  却能够勘测到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their bizarrely shaped nose can detect fresh growth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几百公里外的青草长势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}from hundreds of miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.35,0:05:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这两只小羊即将与其他草原动物一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The young twins will now begin the nomadic life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.85,0:05:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始辽阔草原上不断迁徙的生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they share with most animals on the world's open plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.36,0:05:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,降雨量不足以养育森林时就会出现草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grasslands occur where rain is too sporadic for forests to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草原生长所需的年降雨量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rain that a grassland needs to survive for a year
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.40,0:05:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会一次来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}might arrive all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.18,0:06:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样的暴雨在二十四小时内能达到三百毫米降雨量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Storms like these can release 12 inches of rain in 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.61,0:06:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,淋起来可不好受\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not much fun if you're out in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终土壤无法继续吸收雨水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eventually the earth can't soak up any more,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.10,0:06:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草原也完全变了样子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the grassland undergoes a radical change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.67,0:07:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多植物会被淹死  而草本却会茁壮生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many plants would drown here, but grasses thrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.58,0:07:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们长得飞快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They grow so fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,茎叶迅速伸出水面  沐浴在阳光下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their leaves quickly rise above the water and into the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.20,0:07:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在南非\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here in southern Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.12,0:07:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,降水能让世界上最奇特的草原之一改头换面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}water transforms one of the most remarkable grasslands on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥卡万戈三角洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Okavango.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年都有近一万三千平方公里的草原被水淹没\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every year, 5,000 square miles of grassland are flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于狮群来说  这成了最大的问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For one pride of lions, this poses a major problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.00,0:07:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然猎物众多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There may be plenty of prey around,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.65,0:08:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但狮子并不擅长在水中捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but lions struggle to run it down in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.91,0:08:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮群中有三个月的幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The pride has three-month-old cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.79,0:08:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们以前从未见过水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've never seen water before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.82,0:08:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果母狮们短时间内捕不到猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If their mothers don't make a kill soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些幼崽可能撑不过这周\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the cubs might not survive the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,受洪水滋养\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But fuelled by the flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.92,0:08:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蓬勃生长的青草吸引来新的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the eruption of grass attracts new possible prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数量超过两千头的水牛群接踵而至\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Buffalo arrive in herds 2,000 strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.20,0:08:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强大  好斗  抱团前进\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Powerful, aggressive and united,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.69,0:08:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮子能遇到的动物中  水牛是最危险的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they're the most dangerous animal a lion can face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.70,0:09:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体型最大的公牛不会逃跑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The biggest bulls don't run.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们仗着身形庞大  并不惧怕狮子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're simply too huge to be scared of lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重达九百公斤  他比五头母狮加起来都重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At 900 kilos, he weighs more than all five lionesses combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然狮群占据了数量优势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The pride do have numbers on their side,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.28,0:10:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果被水牛角扫到  可能会直接丧命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but one sweep of his horns could be deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一头母狮正面诱敌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One distracts the bull up front,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.79,0:10:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的姐妹从后方进攻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}while her sisters attack from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母狮们必须想办法压倒公牛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cats must somehow topple the buffalo,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.14,0:10:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但沼泽太过湿滑  脚底无法借力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but with swamp under foot, they can't get any traction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.34,0:11:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,公牛逐渐虚弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bull is weakening,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.01,0:11:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但狮群也露出疲态\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the lions are tiring, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是体力与毅力的双重考验\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now a battle of will as much as strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要想活下去  公牛必须想办法甩掉母狮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To live, the bull must somehow shake off the lioness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.58,0:12:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这头公牛受了伤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bull is wounded,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但幸亏有五厘米厚的牛皮  他会慢慢痊愈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but thanks to his two-inch-thick hide, he will recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.21,0:12:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而狮群  只能忍饥挨饿了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the pride, these are hungry times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但等到水位降低  便会有新生命来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But, ultimately, once the water recedes, there will be new life,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:13:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也就有了新的食物来源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and new food to benefit all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.96,0:13:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要条件适宜  草本植物可以在短短几天内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the right conditions, grasses have the extraordinary ability
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完成从发芽到开花的全过程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to grow from first shoots to flower in a matter of only days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青草变成一棵棵微型果树\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grasses become the miniature equivalents of fruiting trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.02,0:13:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于住在其中的生物来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And for creatures living within the grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样的草丛就像雨林一样高大葱郁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this is a landscape as vast and towering as any rainforest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.78,0:13:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常适合建造小树屋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And excellent place to build a tiny tree house
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,供巢鼠居住\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for a harvest mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.98,0:14:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏季的欧洲草原食物充盈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During summer, European meadowlands are full of food,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.97,0:14:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只看谁能捷足先登\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but only for those that can reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爬草比爬树更困难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Climbing grass is harder than climbing trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主要是因为草茎不会静止不动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}not least because their stems just won't stay still.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.13,0:14:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的尾巴可以抓握物体  就像第五只手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her prehensile tail acts like a fifth limb,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:15:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让她如林中穿梭的猴子一般敏捷灵活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so she's as agile as a monkey clambering around in a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和森林中一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And just as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片草丛中最好的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the best food in this tiny forest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.23,0:15:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也在植株最顶端\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is at the very top of its canopy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.35,0:15:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但爬到高处觅食  就会暴露自己\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Feeding up here, she's exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只仓鸮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A barn owl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动作不算灵巧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not her finest move...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.39,0:16:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但也算成功逃命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it did the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巢鼠鲜少在地面行动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Harvest mice seldom go all the way down to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.08,0:16:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的世界复杂而危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a tangled and dangerous world down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.19,0:16:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她能够通过解读头顶的草茎来辨明方向\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But she can read the pattern of the stems overhead like a map,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.84,0:16:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从而找到回家的路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and so find her way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时机刚好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And not a minute too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽嗷嗷待哺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are mouths to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.88,0:17:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的宝宝们必须迅速长大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her babies must fatten up quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要趁着夏季食物充盈时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They need to harvest the summer grasses
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.17,0:17:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽量进食成长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}while they're still rich with food.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非洲稀树草原亦是如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On the African savannah, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应季时草地生命丰富多彩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}seasonal grasses are filled with life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.35,0:17:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但却不会持续太久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红喉蜂虎是卓越的空中猎手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Carmine bee-eaters are superb aerial hunters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.77,0:18:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十分擅长捕食飞行中的昆虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}experts at catching insects in midair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它们无法将猎物赶出草丛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they have no way of flushing their prey out of the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦警觉起来  大多数昆虫会静止不动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once alarmed, most insects stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.97,0:18:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,红喉蜂虎需要找帮手来捣乱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bee-eaters need someone to stir things up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.86,0:18:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只灰颈鹭鸨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A kori bustard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.38,0:18:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它是世界上体重最大的飞禽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the world's heaviest flying bird,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凭它庞大的身躯  应该能轰出一些虫子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so it should be bulky enough to kick up some insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成功了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到有别的蜂虎加入\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Until someone else comes along
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打乱它的计划\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and cramps your style.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.47,0:19:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没关系  也许等会还有更好的机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Never mind, perhaps there are bigger opportunities ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.02,0:19:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸵鸟怎么样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What about an ostrich?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.51,0:19:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是体重最大的鸟类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The heaviest bird of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次有足够的交通工具了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This time there's more than enough transport to go around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.32,0:19:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快  几乎每只鸵鸟都有了自己的乘客\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon, almost every ostrich has its own passenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过搭便车的也得意不了多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But free riders are only tolerated for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.37,0:20:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蜂虎真正需要的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What the bee-eaters really need
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.39,0:20:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是体型大到根本注意不到它们的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is a creature so big it won't even notice them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非洲公象夷平草地之势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nothing cuts a swathe through grass
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有动物能与之比肩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}like an African bull elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诀窍是尽可能飞在这位“大块头”的近前方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The trick is to fly as close to the front of the giant as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.56,0:20:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想取得奖赏  必须在刹那间出手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They only have a split second to grab the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.05,0:21:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越来越多昆虫被赶出来  竞争也愈发激烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As more insects are stirred up, the competition intensifies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.24,0:21:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏天即将结束  储备食物的竞赛已然打响\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With summer drawing to a close, the race to stock up is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.27,0:21:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草很快就会枯萎  屯食良机转瞬即逝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon, the grass will wither, and this opportunity will have gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.48,0:22:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了旱季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the dry season takes hold,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.23,0:22:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地面的食物愈发稀缺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}food becomes increasingly thin on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.72,0:22:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有在真正身怀绝技的草原捕猎者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, only the most specialised predators on the plains
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.79,0:22:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能维持生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can make a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.60,0:22:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她虽然形似猎豹  但这只猫并非短跑能手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She may be spotted like a cheetah, but this cat is no sprinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.85,0:22:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相反  修长的四肢给予她独特的猎捕优势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Instead, she has extra-long legs which give her a high vantage point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.76,0:23:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过薮猫最主要的武器  是她雷达般的双耳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But a serval cat's main weapon are enormous radar ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.66,0:23:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能精确定位草丛中猎物的藏身之处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They help her pinpoint prey hiding in the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.99,0:23:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是她的猎物十分机警\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the prey she seeks are canny.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.09,0:23:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非洲沟齿沼鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Southern vlei rats.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.86,0:23:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们知道持续移动会暴露行踪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They know that any sustained movement can give them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.30,0:23:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是选择短距离爆冲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So they move in short bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是最细微的窸窣声也会被薮猫察觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even the slightest rustle will give her a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.97,0:24:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快找到了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.84,0:24:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更接近了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.99,0:24:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没抓到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.75,0:26:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形势好的时候  她一天能抓十只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In better times, she could catch 10 a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.34,0:26:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但现在啮齿动物数量极少  她只能挨饿了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but now, with so few rodents around, she will have to go hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.64,0:26:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着干旱加剧  草原生活更加艰难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As drought intensifies, life gets tougher for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.36,0:26:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,定居于此的捕食者只能选择熬过去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Predators with permanent territories must tough it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.00,0:26:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为大部分猎物都已远去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}while most of their prey disappear over the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.38,0:26:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了抵御饥饿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To avoid starvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.11,0:26:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草原动物大多随水草迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}many grassland animals follow a nomadic way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.64,0:26:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,超过两百万头牛羚奔走在东非大草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over 2,000,000 wildebeests wander the East African savannahs
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.89,0:27:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,追逐着雨水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}chasing the rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.01,0:27:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过它们并不孤单\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they are not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.47,0:27:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,展翅飞来这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Arriving on the wing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.17,0:27:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰氏巧织雀也在寻找鲜嫩的草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Jackson's Widowbirds also seek fresh grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.13,0:27:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而  它们却不只是为食物而来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Although, it's not just food that they're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.42,0:27:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只雄鸟想求偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This male wants a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.04,0:27:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为此他已长出漂亮的繁殖羽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's grown elaborate breeding plumage for this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.16,0:27:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他需要舞台来展现自我\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he needs a stage on which to show it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.90,0:27:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,细心挑选草茎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By carefully selecting grass blades,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.31,0:27:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每一根修剪到合适的长度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}each trimmed to the correct length,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.93,0:28:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正在进行非常独特的创作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he's creating something very special.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.79,0:28:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他需要一块平地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He needs an even surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.59,0:28:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和一个中央摆设\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and a centre-piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,舞台已经布置好了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The stage is set.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.68,0:28:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的单身公寓干净整洁  很能吸引雌鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His bachelor pad is sufficiently neat and tidy to attract a female.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.35,0:28:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问题是\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The problem is,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.01,0:28:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她能看到吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can she see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.28,0:28:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还有竞争对手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He has competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.24,0:28:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,园艺设计可能不足以打动女士们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It might take more than a little gardening to impress the ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.23,0:29:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跳起来是个好办法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Jumping is the right idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.54,0:29:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他低估了草的高度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he's misjudged the height of the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的对手显得很轻松\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His rival makes it look easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.55,0:29:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他得加把劲了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Time to raise his game.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.87,0:30:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅要看谁跳得高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not only who jumps the highest,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.34,0:30:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还要看谁能跳得久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but who can keep doing so the longest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.21,0:30:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对手们无法坚持下去  相继退出竞争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unable to go the distance, his rivals drop out one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.19,0:30:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的耐力吸引了爱侣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Stamina has won him admirers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.79,0:30:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在可以展示他的求爱舞台了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}now he can show off his courtship arena...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.89,0:31:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来一场浪漫的捉迷藏游戏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And engage in a little romantic hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.14,0:31:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他终于得偿所愿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Finally, he's done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.06,0:31:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,东非大草原养育着成千上万的食草动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The East African savannahs support millions of grazers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.81,0:31:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年会吃掉数百万吨草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each year they devour millions of tons of grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.93,0:31:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而有一种生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and yet there's one creature here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.10,0:31:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对草原造成的影响  远大于其他动物的总和\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}whose impact is far greater than all these animals combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.42,0:32:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上有草的地方  都有它们的踪影\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're found wherever grass grows on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.32,0:32:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它们的辛苦劳作几乎难以察觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}yet their labours go almost entirely unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.80,0:32:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中最出色的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One of the most remarkable is found here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.79,0:32:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出现在南美洲草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on the grasslands of South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.58,0:32:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些叶片十分坚硬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These blades are so tough
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.83,0:32:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎没有大型食草动物能消化得了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that virtually no large grass eaters can stomach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.81,0:32:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而却被小小的切叶蚁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet they're harvested on an industrial scale...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.77,0:32:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大规模采集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...by tiny grass cutter ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.77,0:32:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可它们根本无法消化叶片\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they themselves can't digest one bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.02,0:32:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那到底是为什么呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, why bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.92,0:33:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,答案在地下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The answer is underground,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.66,0:33:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可谓别出心裁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and it's very ingenious.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.68,0:33:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每根叶片都被切成一定长度  放入菌圃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each blade is cut to length and placed into a garden of fungus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.42,0:33:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真菌以腐烂的叶片为食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rotting grass feeds the fungus,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.41,0:33:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而真菌又成为蚂蚁的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and in turn the fungus feeds the ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.84,0:33:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,养活五百万劳动者需要大规模的高效耕作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But feeding 5,000,000 workers requires intensive agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.10,0:33:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸好它们都很勤劳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Luckily, they are an industrious lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.10,0:33:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅这一个蚁群  每年就能收集五百多公斤草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This colony alone will collect over half a ton of grass every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.59,0:34:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数十亿蚁群遍布全球草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With billions of ant colonies across the world's grasslands
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.20,0:34:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都在做相同的事\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}all doing exactly the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.93,0:34:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们消耗的草数量惊人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that's a mind-boggling amount of grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.32,0:34:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据估计  地球上超过三分之一的草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's estimated that over one third of the grass that grows on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.93,0:34:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都会被这种昆虫采去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will be harvested by an insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.05,0:34:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在澳大利亚北部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In northern Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.65,0:34:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白蚁辛勤的劳作体现在雕塑上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}termites memorialise their industry in sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.89,0:35:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些令人叹为观止的白蚁丘有三米高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These astonishing mounds are 10 feet tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.32,0:35:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全部建成南北走向\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're always built on a north-south axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.51,0:35:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因此它们的建筑者被称为罗盘白蚁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which is why their builders are called compass termites.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.05,0:35:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些粘土造就的城堡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These castles of clay
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.91,0:35:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保护着它们的主人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}protect their builders from extremes of heat
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.79,0:35:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不受草原酷暑和季节性洪水的伤害\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and seasonal floods experienced on many grasslands.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.87,0:35:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白蚁与大多数食草动物不同\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Termites manage to do what most grass eaters can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.47,0:35:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们能分解枯草  提取养分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}break down dead grass and extract the nutrients.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.30,0:36:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但也有动物能探进蚁穴将它们吃掉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they themselves can be food for those that can reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.28,0:36:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,六十厘米长的舌头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A two-foot-long tongue
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.73,0:36:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上面布满极小的钩子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}covered in microscopic hooks,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.51,0:36:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加之比迅猛龙还要长的爪子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}followed by claws longer than those of a velociraptor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.33,0:36:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一只生活在南美平原上的大食蚁兽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A giant anteater on the plains of South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.18,0:36:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它每天可以吞食两万只昆虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It can devour 20,000 insects a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.82,0:36:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有力的前肢让它们能够轻易地掰开白蚁巢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Powerful forelegs enable it to rip apart a termite hill with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.68,0:37:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳炙烤草原  白蚁面临着新的危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And as the sun bakes the grass, the termites face new danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几分钟内  大火就将草原化为灰烬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In minutes, fire turns grassland to ash.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.77,0:37:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是草不会被大火烧尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the grasses are not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.54,0:37:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的地下茎完好无损\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their underground stems are unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.95,0:38:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数周  数月就这么过去了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Weeks, months may pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.87,0:38:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是雨季终将来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but eventually the rains will return
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.73,0:38:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青草又会重新发芽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the grass will sprout again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.31,0:38:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一些草原不仅要忍受火的炙烤  还有冰霜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some grasslands must endure not only fire, but ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.20,0:38:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冬季来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As winter approaches,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.91,0:38:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北美的草原开始霜冻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the prairies of North America begin to freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.82,0:38:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏季  美洲野牛四处漫步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In summer, bison roamed freely,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.46,0:38:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,享用着取之不尽的大片青草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}almost continuously cropping the abundant green grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.22,0:38:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在青草不仅枯萎结冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, that grass is not only withered and frozen,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.92,0:39:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上还会被大雪掩埋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's about to be buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.15,0:39:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,六千万吨的积雪覆盖在野牛群的领地上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sixty million tons of snow now blanket this herd's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.15,0:39:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在厚厚的积雪中行动非常耗费体力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pushing through deep snow is exhausting work,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.56,0:39:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美洲野牛越来越饥饿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the bison are now slowly starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.67,0:39:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅保暖都需要耗费大量的能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Just keeping warm saps huge amounts of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.61,0:40:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们厚重的皮毛可耐受零下三十度的低温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their thick coats can insulate them down to minus 20 Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.99,0:40:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是零下四十度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now minus 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.22,0:40:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一能让他们活下去的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The only thing that will keep them alive
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.11,0:40:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被深埋在一米深的积雪之下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is buried beneath three feet of snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.93,0:40:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们意想不到的邻居也面临着同样的问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And that's a problem shared with a surprising neighbour.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.22,0:40:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狐狸在搜寻的食物也被深埋在积雪之下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The food the fox seeks is also deep beneath the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.92,0:40:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这两种生物能否生存下去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The survival of both creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.11,0:41:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,取决于能否挖到地面的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}depends on getting through to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.54,0:41:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于美洲野牛来说  用蛮力就可以做到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the bison, it will be a matter of brute strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.19,0:41:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强大的颈部肌肉让他们每天可以铲五吨的雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Massive neck muscles enable them to shovel five tonnes of snow a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.95,0:41:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们小巧的邻居则需要更高的准头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their light-weight neighbour needs more precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美洲野牛达到了目的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bison have reached their goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.50,0:42:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一大口枯草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a mouthful of withered grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.07,0:42:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在美洲野牛挖过的地方狐狸也见缝插针\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And where the bison have dug, the fox now spots an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.05,0:42:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每一步都至关重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every footstep counts,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.21,0:42:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是时机...\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he mustn't break through...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.13,0:42:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还未到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.46,0:42:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他仔细监听着猎物的一举一动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He listens carefully to pinpoint his target.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.99,0:42:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它在移动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.63,0:43:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只野鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A vole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.30,0:43:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然小  但是比一嘴干草的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Small, but 100 times more nutritious
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.72,0:43:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,营养价值高上百倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}than a mouthful of dried grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.83,0:43:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要在这草原上度过严冬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To get through the winter on these prairies,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.56,0:43:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候脑子比蛮力更加重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sometimes brain beats brawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.14,0:43:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终  所有草原上的生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ultimately, life on all grasslands
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.32,0:43:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都依赖于季节的更迭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}depends on the turn of the seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.75,0:44:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在树木生存极限八百公里以北的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Five hundred miles further north than any tree can survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.00,0:44:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青草春风吹又生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grass returns to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.40,0:44:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性北美驯鹿远赴北方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Caribou females have journeyed to the far north
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.54,0:44:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来此产仔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to calve.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,超过七万只驯鹿幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over 70,000 caribou babies
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.61,0:44:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将在几天内出生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will be born in the next few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.66,0:44:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小鹿出生的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the calves appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.37,0:44:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也正是青草发新芽的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so too do the leaves of the newly sprouting grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.33,0:44:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼鹿必须迅速增强体能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the calves must strengthen quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.86,0:45:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几天内他们就将跟随自己的父母\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Within days they will have to keep up with their parents
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.34,0:45:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,踏上无尽的征程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on a never-ending march.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.19,0:45:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一天  他们的速度就已经超过人类短跑健将\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At one day old, they're already faster than an Olympic sprinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.24,0:45:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们正在测试自己跋山涉水用的四肢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're testing the legs that will carry them thousands of miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.91,0:45:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好现在就知道极限在哪里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}better to learn their limitations now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.98,0:45:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看起来很好玩  但草原上最艰苦的生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It may look playful, but there's no harder life on the grasslands
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.30,0:45:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正等着这些他们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}than that facing these infants.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.64,0:45:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母驯鹿现在聚集起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The caribou mothers now join together,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.09,0:46:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每只都带着一只同样大小的幼鹿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}each with an infant exactly the same age.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.35,0:46:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们准备启程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're setting off on the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.27,0:46:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进行陆地上最伟大的长途跋涉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}overland trek made by any animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.75,0:46:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是无论草食性动物走到哪里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But wherever grass eaters travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.84,0:46:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都有捕食者等待着他们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}predators lie in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.16,0:46:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是他们  北极狼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here they are, Arctic wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.63,0:47:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们必须要在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They must seize their chance
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.55,0:47:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,驯鹿经过领地时把握住机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}while the caribou pass through their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.61,0:47:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北极狼跑向鹿群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The wolf runs at the herd,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.87,0:47:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,试图冲散群体中的弱者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}trying to flush out the weak or the slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.51,0:48:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只幼鹿走散了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A calf is separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.76,0:48:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼全力以赴捕猎的时速将近六十公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At full tilt, 40 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.61,0:48:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只比小鹿快一点点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the wolf is just faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.31,0:48:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是幼鹿的耐力更好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the calf has stamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.73,0:48:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然只有几周大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only a few weeks old,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.94,0:49:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只幼鹿的求生欲望让人叹为观止\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and this calf's will to survive is remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.93,0:49:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且必须如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it needs to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.28,0:49:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些幼鹿开始了一场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for these young caribou have now started a journey
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.80,0:49:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终其一生的旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that will last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.24,0:49:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远追寻着他们所需要的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Forever chasing the seasonal growth of the grass
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.80,0:49:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,季节性生长的青草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on which they depend.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.65,0:49:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和其他草原生物一样  他们依赖着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like all grassland creatures, they are at the mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.93,0:49:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这变化莫测而又极其慷慨的大草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of these unpredictable but ultimately bountiful lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.13,0:49:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青草可以在地球上最为极端的环境下生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass can survive some of the harshest conditions on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.37,0:49:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经受洪水  火灾和冰霜的考验仍然生机盎然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}flood, fire and frost, and still flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.48,0:50:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以草原为地球上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So it is that grasslands provide a stage
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.17,0:50:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最壮观的野生动物群提供了舞台\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the greatest gatherings of wildlife on planet earth.
